      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KAY JAY MIKI (3) put the writing on the wall with back-to-back placings then drew on the second row but made up plenty of ground to get the prize by 1.4 metres at his latest appearance at Penrith. Likely to get the favours from this nice draw so could strike again. CAPTAIN JAZZ (2) has improved with each start since a long spell, culminating in a comfortable victory by 8 metres at Wagga last week. That took her record at this distance range to 50 per cent and she draws well so could go back to back. ITS DOWN TO DIGGER (7) has been midfield in tougher races at Bathurst in both outings since a second at Canberra. Draws for a trail and could be dangerous if he gets the gaps. YARRAMAN TILLY (1) has been coming from the second line of late so is better served by the ace draw.",
